  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ijwi ry&apos;Abahinzi n&apos;Aborozi (Farmers Voice Project)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ER 1: Agricultural oriented CSOs are better equipped to engage farmers and advocate for their rights in targeted regions
ER 2: Capacities of the District Farmers&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122; Network in representing farmers&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122; interests, rights and needs are strengthened
ER3: Improved collaboration and coordination among agricultural oriented CSOs at national level for improved level of influence over policies and decision making.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers in Rutsiro (Western Province), Burera  (northern Province), Rubavu (Western Province) and Gatsibo (Eastern province)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The action&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s overall objective is to contribute to the reduction of poverty and strengthened food security by promoting farmer centred policies through enhanced civil society and farmers&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122; organisations engagement in Rwanda.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x153;Ijwi ry&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;Abahinzi n&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;Aborozi&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x9D; (Farmer&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s Voices) Project aims to tackle this head on by strengthening the participatory research and advocacy capacities of existing civil society bodies working on food security (including farmer cooperatives, value chain associations and research organisations) and creating mutually compatible District Farmers Network (DFN) that offer a space for farmers to voice their concerns and recommendations. At present most farmer cooperatives and unions are organised around specific commodities (i.e. maize, rice, Irish potatoes, coffee, tea). Opportunities to collaborate across sectors are missed. Through this action, the DFN will bring together different farmer cooperatives, unions and informal groups, agro-dealers, and Twigire Muhinzi extension workers, to combine advocacy campaigns and hone their mobilization around a small number of specific national level policy issues to bring about a wider change.</narrative>
  </description>
